description.en:
Introduction into the main methods used in plant physiology. The course gives the theoretical basis for the experiments and practical skills needed to perform respective experiments.

Topics include:
- Absorption spectra and determination of analyte concentration by spectrophotometry
- The acid-base properties of amino acids and buffer solutions
- Basic protein separation and purification techniques
- Basics of enzyme kinetics
- the estimation of compounds (photosynthetic pigments,  phenolics) and activities of enzymes (nitrate reductase, water photooxidation complex) characteristic for plants;
- measurement of the photosynthetic electron transport rate and water metabolism parameters;
- the estimation of soil water capacity and pH;
- the acquisition of basic statistical data analysis techniques.
